The paper discusses the security of Trust Management (TM) systems for authentication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also explores the use of blockchain technology, which is a distributed computing paradigm (cs.DC) and has been widely used in the field of cybersecurity. The paper also discusses the formal modeling of TM systems, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses attacks on TM systems, which is related to cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of using blockchain technology, which is related to distributed ledger technology (cs.DL).
